{"title":"Ritchey Introduces the Redesigned P-29er XC Mountain Bike","link":"https://theradavist.com/redesigned-p-29er-xc-mountain-bike/","date":1718295101000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-23.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-23.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-23.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-23.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-23.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>Previewed in our <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/ritchey-montebello-randonneuring-bike-outback-p-29er-frames-and-more/\" target=\"_blank\">Sea Otter Classic coverage</a> earlier this year, the new Ritchey P-29er is finally available. After perfecting his concept for a new mountain bike, Tom introduced the first P-29er in 2012. Now, Ritchey announces the latest <a href=\"https://ritcheydesign.pxf.io/nLmLBA\">updated version of the P-29er</a>, the latest manifestation of Ritchey’s deep heritage of mountain bike history.</em></p>\n<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-7.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-7.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-7.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-7.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-7.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>With its pedigree firmly rooted in the decades-deep lineage of its P-series predecessors, this version of the P-29er is very much a contemporary machine with features demanded by today’s XC riders. Like all Ritchey frames, the P29er is built with proprietary triple-butted Logic steel tubing, now with stealthy dropper post routing and an ultralight forged machined tapered headtube. It boasts BOOST spacing and clears tires up to 2.3”.</p>\n<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-23.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-23.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-23.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-23.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-23.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-28.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-28.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-28.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-28.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-28.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-21.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-21.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-21.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-21.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-21.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Its modern XC geometry, delivers a breathtakingly balanced ride, however if you want to make old trails new again, forego suspension and opt for a rigid fork to get extra rowdy. Or pair it with a super compact drop bar and go even farther afield, including the urban landscape. All of this comes together to enshrine the P-29er as a monument to the spirit of endless possibility, redesigning what riders expect from a hardtail.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-24.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-24.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-24.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-24.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-24.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Tom Ritchey is known for taking whatever bike project he’s working on to the limit and then pushing beyond that in the redesign phase. This latest P-29er perfectly demonstrates his indisputable design style and his tendency toward new thinking to make something great even better.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-6.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-6.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-6.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-6.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-6.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-14.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-14.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-14.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-14.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-19.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-19.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-19.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-19.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-19.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Ritchey P-29 Quick Hits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Frame cost: $999 USD</li>\n<li>Material: Heat-treated, triple-butted Ritchey Logic steel tubing – TIG welded</li>\n<li>Headset: WCS headset included (upper IS42/28.6 | lower IS52/40)</li>\n<li>Seat Tube: 27.2mm with stealth dropper routing</li>\n<li>Bottom bracket: 73mm – English threaded</li>\n<li>Crankset maximum ring size: 38T single / Designed for 1X chainrings</li>\n<li>Chainline: 52mm / Replaceable stainless-steel derailleur hanger</li>\n<li>Recommended tire size: 29×2.25 (2.3 max) – tire size varies by rim and tire manufacturer</li>\n<li>Post-mount rear brake: 160mm (180mm max – adaptors available separately)</li>\n<li>Bottle cage mounts: Two (one on downtube and one on seat tube) *Note: size small frames include only a downtube bottle</li>\n<li>cage mount</li>\n<li>Sizes: S (15″) / M (17″) / L (19″) / XL (20.5″)</li>\n<li>Weight: 2,315g (M/17″)</li>\n<li>Color: Dirt in Blood</li>\n<li>Spacing: BOOST 148mm spacing (12mm alloy thru-axle included) / Optimized for 120mm (BOOST) suspension travel fork or 500mm axle-crown rigid fork</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-13.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-13.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-13.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-13.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Ritchey-P29er-XC-MTB-Build-Permutations-13.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://ritcheydesign.pxf.io/nLmLBA\" target=\"_blank\">Ritchey</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/redesigned-p-29er-xc-mountain-bike/\">Ritchey Introduces the Redesigned P-29er XC Mountain Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"Josh Weinberg","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"6d0f16a39a34bd646a47a49e5ad80889efd1f7d902bbd2994a022afdbe118bba","category":"Cycling"}